1
00:00:41,097 --> 00:00:43,444
<font face="Comic Sans MS">May I ask you something?</font>

2
00:00:43,478 --> 00:00:46,102
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I can't promise I'll answer.</font>

3
00:00:47,655 --> 00:00:51,383
<font face="Comic Sans MS">R... right, that's exactly
what I meant.</font>

4
00:00:51,417 --> 00:00:55,145
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Um, are you allowed to speak
along the way?</font>

5
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:57,975
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I was thinking
there might be rules.</font>

6
00:00:58,010 --> 00:00:59,770
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Let me put it this way</font>

7
00:00:59,805 --> 00:01:04,189
<font face="Comic Sans MS">very few make it all the way
without uttering a word.</font>

8
00:01:04,223 --> 00:01:07,606
<font face="Comic Sans MS">People are overcome with
a strange and sudden need</font>

9
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:10,298
<font face="Comic Sans MS">to confess on these trips.</font>

10
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,473
<font face="Comic Sans MS">And not all of it
can be said to be</font>

11
00:01:12,507 --> 00:01:15,096
<font face="Comic Sans MS">of great rhetorical quality</font>

12
00:01:15,131 --> 00:01:18,444
<font face="Comic Sans MS">but do carry on merrily</font>

13
00:01:18,479 --> 00:01:21,654
<font face="Comic Sans MS">just don't believe you're
going to tell me something</font>

14
00:01:21,689 --> 00:01:23,725
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I haven't heard before.</font>

15
00:01:33,459 --> 00:01:36,186
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I will tentatively
divide my tale</font>

16
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:39,534
<font face="Comic Sans MS">into 5 randomly
chosen incidents</font>

17
00:01:39,569 --> 00:01:41,743
<font face="Comic Sans MS">over a 12-year period.</font>

18
00:02:08,529 --> 00:02:12,049
<font face="Comic Sans MS">So I'm standing here
holding this jack</font>

19
00:02:12,084 --> 00:02:14,569
<font face="Comic Sans MS">crap's not working.</font>

20
00:02:14,604 --> 00:02:17,193
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Do you, uh, do you have a jack
I could borrow?</font>

21
00:02:17,227 --> 00:02:19,505
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No, I'm sorry.</font>

22
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:21,024
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- No?
- No</font>

23
00:02:21,058 --> 00:02:22,715
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- No?
- No</font>

24
00:02:24,372 --> 00:02:28,135
<font face="Comic Sans MS">That's odd,
I thought everyone had a jack.</font>

25
00:02:28,169 --> 00:02:30,033
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I don't.</font>

26
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:32,553
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Perhaps you could
have a look at my car?</font>

27
00:02:34,210 --> 00:02:37,868
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well, I don't have to
have a look at your car.</font>

28
00:02:37,903 --> 00:02:40,768
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The issue with your jack
is it's broken.</font>

29
00:02:40,802 --> 00:02:42,045
<font face="Comic Sans MS">There.</font>

30
00:02:44,668 --> 00:02:49,604
<font face="Comic Sans MS">So, uh, what's a person
like me supposed to do?</font>

31
00:02:49,639 --> 00:02:53,470
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well, I suppose</font>

32
00:02:53,505 --> 00:02:57,371
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I could, uh, drive over
to Sonny's repair shop</font>

33
00:02:57,405 --> 00:02:59,821
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and call for roadside
assistance.</font>

34
00:02:59,856 --> 00:03:03,170
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's about, uh,
5 miles from here.</font>

35
00:03:03,204 --> 00:03:04,654
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What kind of repair shop is it?</font>

36
00:03:04,688 --> 00:03:07,001
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's... it's..
Sonny's a blacksmith, very good one.</font>

37
00:03:07,035 --> 00:03:09,279
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Blacksmith.</font>

38
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:13,076
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well, maybe this Sonny can
repair the jack?</font>

39
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:15,147
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You'd have to talk to Sonny
about that.</font>

40
00:03:16,562 --> 00:03:19,738
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Perhaps, I could entice you
to drive me there?</font>

41
00:03:19,772 --> 00:03:21,912
<font face="Comic Sans MS">- Please.
- Um..</font>

42
00:03:44,038 --> 00:03:46,937
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Oops, that was a mistake.</font>

43
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,595
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Mistake?</font>

44
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:52,288
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Me getting in this car
with you.</font>

45
00:03:52,322 --> 00:03:53,472
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What was it one's mother
used to say</font>

46
00:03:53,496 --> 00:03:56,775
<font face="Comic Sans MS">about not getting into cars
with strangers?</font>

47
00:03:56,809 --> 00:03:58,984
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well..</font>

48
00:03:59,018 --> 00:04:01,814
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I wouldn't know what
your mother said.</font>

49
00:04:01,849 --> 00:04:03,471
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You might as well be
a serial killer.</font>

50
00:04:05,059 --> 00:04:07,130
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm sorry but you do kind of
look like one.</font>

51
00:04:09,028 --> 00:04:10,754
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You'd like me
to drive you back to your car?</font>

52
00:04:12,308 --> 00:04:14,931
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No, no.
I can take care of myself.</font>

53
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:18,762
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm sorry,
were you offended</font>

54
00:04:18,797 --> 00:04:20,626
<font face="Comic Sans MS">that I called you
a serial killer?</font>

55
00:04:21,869 --> 00:04:22,973
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No.</font>

56
00:04:24,251 --> 00:04:27,081
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's of absolutely
no importance to me.</font>

57
00:04:30,464 --> 00:04:32,742
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Maybe it's just the van.</font>

58
00:04:32,776 --> 00:04:36,263
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's the kind one might expect
to be kidnapped in</font>

59
00:04:36,297 --> 00:04:38,817
<font face="Comic Sans MS">or used to transport corpses.</font>

60
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:42,648
<font face="Comic Sans MS">But if you really were
a serial killer</font>

61
00:04:42,683 --> 00:04:43,970
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I guess the easiest thing
would be just</font>

62
00:04:43,994 --> 00:04:48,930
<font face="Comic Sans MS">to bury my body back up there
by those trees</font>

63
00:04:48,965 --> 00:04:51,174
<font face="Comic Sans MS">but you'd have to remember
to dig 6 feet down</font>

64
00:04:51,208 --> 00:04:53,314
<font face="Comic Sans MS">so the foxes couldn't
dig up my grave.</font>

65
00:04:55,627 --> 00:04:58,388
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What would I do?</font>

66
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:01,288
<font face="Comic Sans MS">What would I do to keep you
from getting away with it?</font>

67
00:05:02,979 --> 00:05:06,293
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Of course, I'd just</font>

68
00:05:06,327 --> 00:05:09,330
<font face="Comic Sans MS">pick up that jack and hit you
over the head with it.</font>

69
00:05:09,365 --> 00:05:11,194
<font face="Comic Sans MS">A jack like that can do quite
a bit of damage</font>

70
00:05:11,228 --> 00:05:12,437
<font face="Comic Sans MS">don't you think?</font>

71
00:05:14,818 --> 00:05:16,544
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm not a medical examiner.</font>

72
00:05:16,579 --> 00:05:18,960
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It'd do quite a lot of damage.</font>

73
00:05:39,602 --> 00:05:43,433
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Don't forget this.
Good luck with Sonny.</font>

74
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:47,092
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Um, would it be too much to ask
for you to drive me back?</font>

75
00:05:47,126 --> 00:05:49,128
<font face="Comic Sans MS">If this Sonny is as fast as
you say he is?</font>

76
00:05:51,890 --> 00:05:54,168
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm sure Sonny is perfectly
capable of giving you</font>

77
00:05:54,202 --> 00:05:55,687
<font face="Comic Sans MS">a lift back to your..</font>

78
00:05:55,721 --> 00:05:57,792
<font face="Comic Sans MS">As... as I told you before,
I don't like</font>

79
00:05:57,827 --> 00:05:59,138
<font face="Comic Sans MS">driving with strangers.</font>

80
00:06:01,037 --> 00:06:03,453
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well, I'm just as much of
a stranger as Sonny is.</font>

81
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:04,868
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Oh, getting along just fine.</font>

82
00:06:04,903 --> 00:06:06,783
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'll just go speak to Sonny,
just take a moment.</font>

83
00:06:19,573 --> 00:06:20,850
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Sonny.</font>

84
00:06:22,127 --> 00:06:23,887
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Hi, Jack.</font>

85
00:06:23,922 --> 00:06:25,026
<font face="Comic Sans MS">How's it going?</font>

86
00:06:25,061 --> 00:06:26,994
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Well, I was working
on Miller's tractor</font>

87
00:06:27,028 --> 00:06:30,273
<font face="Comic Sans MS">but this lady is being
really persistent.</font>

88
00:06:30,307 --> 00:06:31,343
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You don't say.</font>

89
00:06:42,181 --> 00:06:44,839
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Big mistake.</font>

90
00:06:44,874 --> 00:06:47,300
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The reason serial killers can
roam around free in our country</font>

91
00:06:47,324 --> 00:06:50,673
<font face="Comic Sans MS">is that they have no connection
between themselves</font>

92
00:06:50,707 --> 00:06:52,260
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and their victims.</font>

93
00:06:52,295 --> 00:06:54,815
<font face="Comic Sans MS">So, you just made
a big mistake</font>

94
00:06:54,849 --> 00:06:56,713
<font face="Comic Sans MS">letting Sonny see
the two of us together.</font>

95
00:07:08,691 --> 00:07:11,418
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You know..</font>

96
00:07:11,452 --> 00:07:14,386
<font face="Comic Sans MS">...honestly,
I have more important things</font>

97
00:07:14,421 --> 00:07:16,595
<font face="Comic Sans MS">to be doing with my life</font>

98
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:19,115
<font face="Comic Sans MS">than messing around
with this crap.</font>

99
00:07:19,149 --> 00:07:21,635
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You... you said
he was really good.</font>

100
00:07:21,669 --> 00:07:23,844
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Yeah, well,
I'm sure Sonny was just</font>

101
00:07:23,878 --> 00:07:26,985
<font face="Comic Sans MS">distracted by your
goddamned blabbering.</font>

102
00:07:27,019 --> 00:07:29,228
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Now I have to go,
I have an appointment.</font>

103
00:07:29,263 --> 00:07:30,782
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Appointment,
what appointment?</font>

104
00:07:34,164 --> 00:07:36,235
<font face="Comic Sans MS">That's none of your goddamn
business now, is it?</font>

105
00:07:38,065 --> 00:07:40,239
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You're not just gonna
leave me here.</font>

106
00:07:40,274 --> 00:07:42,621
<font face="Comic Sans MS">In fact, yes, that is kind of
what I was thinking.</font>

107
00:07:45,106 --> 00:07:48,351
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I'm sure there will be another
serial killer passing by</font>

108
00:07:48,385 --> 00:07:50,629
<font face="Comic Sans MS">who can give you a lift
back to Sonny's.</font>

109
00:07:52,389 --> 00:07:56,808
<font face="Comic Sans MS">That is, unless he decides
to kill you first.</font>

110
00:07:59,051 --> 00:08:01,882
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Even if I was to beg you
to drive me back?</font>

111
00:08:01,916 --> 00:08:03,470
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Just a last time?</font>

112
00:08:04,712 --> 00:08:06,196
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Pretty please.</font>

113
00:08:20,728 --> 00:08:22,696
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You know,
I take it all back</font>

114
00:08:22,730 --> 00:08:26,044
<font face="Comic Sans MS">what I said earlier about you
looking like a serial killer.</font>

115
00:08:26,078 --> 00:08:28,771
<font face="Comic Sans MS">No, no, no,
you don't have the disposition</font>

116
00:08:28,805 --> 00:08:30,048
<font face="Comic Sans MS">for that sort of thing.</font>

117
00:08:31,532 --> 00:08:34,846
<font face="Comic Sans MS">You're way too much
of a wimp to murder anyone.</font>

118
00:08:51,172 --> 00:08:54,451
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Oh, dear,
you are a dangerous man</font>

119
00:08:54,486 --> 00:08:57,800
<font face="Comic Sans MS">smacked her with a jack,
did you?</font>

120
00:08:57,834 --> 00:09:00,147
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Honestly, I've heard of
more murders</font>

121
00:09:00,181 --> 00:09:02,908
<font face="Comic Sans MS">than I can count.</font>

122
00:09:02,943 --> 00:09:05,635
<font face="Comic Sans MS">And by the way,
what does this ridiculous man</font>

123
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:07,706
<font face="Comic Sans MS">have to do with anything?</font>

124
00:09:07,741 --> 00:09:09,881
<font face="Comic Sans MS">It's Glenn Gould</font>

125
00:09:09,915 --> 00:09:12,539
<font face="Comic Sans MS">one of the greatest piano
players of our time.</font>

126
00:09:14,023 --> 00:09:15,921
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He represents art.</font>

127
00:09:20,616 --> 00:09:23,860
<font face="Comic Sans MS">So a jack in the face of</font>

128
00:09:23,895 --> 00:09:28,106
<font face="Comic Sans MS">an admittedly unbearable lady
was great art.</font>

129
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:31,523
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Is that what I'm to make of it?</font>

130
00:09:31,558 --> 00:09:34,975
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Dear Mr. Verge,
please give me a chance</font>

131
00:09:35,009 --> 00:09:38,979
<font face="Comic Sans MS">to cast some supplemental
light on the story of the jack.</font>

132
00:09:39,013 --> 00:09:42,776
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The old cathedrals often have
sublime artworks hidden away</font>

133
00:09:42,810 --> 00:09:46,124
<font face="Comic Sans MS">in the darkest corners
for only God to see</font>

134
00:09:46,158 --> 00:09:48,713
<font face="Comic Sans MS">or whatever
one feels like calling</font>

135
00:09:48,747 --> 00:09:50,853
<font face="Comic Sans MS">the great architect
behind it all.</font>

136
00:09:52,302 --> 00:09:54,097
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The same goes for murder.</font>

137
00:09:58,343 --> 00:10:00,621
<font face="Comic Sans MS">When I say cathedrals</font>

138
00:10:00,656 --> 00:10:05,108
<font face="Comic Sans MS">it is first and foremost the
gothic buildings we admire.</font>

139
00:10:05,143 --> 00:10:08,525
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Here elegant, pointed arches
have replaced the earlier</font>

140
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:11,494
<font face="Comic Sans MS">more primitive rounded arches.</font>

141
00:10:11,528 --> 00:10:15,636
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The art of engineering is first
and foremost about statics</font>

142
00:10:15,671 --> 00:10:18,432
<font face="Comic Sans MS">that is so things remain
standing in spite of</font>

143
00:10:18,466 --> 00:10:21,677
<font face="Comic Sans MS">the various forces that impact
the buildings.</font>

144
00:10:21,711 --> 00:10:26,474
<font face="Comic Sans MS">In this way, the pointed arch
created a possibility to build</font>

145
00:10:26,509 --> 00:10:29,823
<font face="Comic Sans MS">much higher
and with much more light</font>

146
00:10:29,857 --> 00:10:33,896
<font face="Comic Sans MS">but most importantly
with less use of material.</font>

147
00:10:33,930 --> 00:10:37,347
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I often say that
the material does the work.</font>

148
00:10:37,382 --> 00:10:40,868
<font face="Comic Sans MS">In other words it has
a kind of will of its own</font>

149
00:10:40,903 --> 00:10:44,044
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and by following it,
the result will be</font>

150
00:10:44,078 --> 00:10:45,459
<font face="Comic Sans MS">the most exquisite.</font>

151
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:49,394
<font face="Comic Sans MS">So the material was the jack</font>

152
00:10:49,428 --> 00:10:53,156
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and it jumped into the lady's
face on its own.</font>

153
00:10:54,951 --> 00:10:56,643
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Art is many things.</font>

154
00:10:58,196 --> 00:11:00,819
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Very convenient and unusual</font>

155
00:11:00,854 --> 00:11:03,442
<font face="Comic Sans MS">in the pile of bad excuses.</font>

156
00:11:03,477 --> 00:11:06,204
<font face="Comic Sans MS">But all of that
is of no interest whatsoever</font>

157
00:11:06,238 --> 00:11:08,344
<font face="Comic Sans MS">unless you're an engineer.</font>

158
00:11:09,621 --> 00:11:11,105
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I am an engineer.</font>

159
00:11:19,113 --> 00:11:22,151
<font face="Comic Sans MS">My mother was of the opinion
that becoming an engineer</font>

160
00:11:22,185 --> 00:11:26,189
<font face="Comic Sans MS">was the more financially
viable choice</font>

161
00:11:26,224 --> 00:11:29,572
<font face="Comic Sans MS">but my really big dream
was to become an architect.</font>

162
00:11:35,164 --> 00:11:37,131
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Right before the lady
and the jack</font>

163
00:11:37,166 --> 00:11:38,926
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I purchased a building lot</font>

164
00:11:38,961 --> 00:11:42,067
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and since
I was my own developer</font>

165
00:11:42,102 --> 00:11:44,725
<font face="Comic Sans MS">due to a substantial
inheritance</font>

166
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:47,624
<font face="Comic Sans MS">no one could keep me
from drawing up</font>

167
00:11:47,659 --> 00:11:50,662
<font face="Comic Sans MS">my own plans
for my own house.</font>

168
00:11:56,737 --> 00:12:00,223
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Engineer or architect</font>

169
00:12:00,258 --> 00:12:04,158
<font face="Comic Sans MS">what I see is an OCD patient
in full bloom.</font>

170
00:12:04,193 --> 00:12:07,058
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Ordnungszwang Jack</font>

171
00:12:07,092 --> 00:12:10,406
<font face="Comic Sans MS">to use a good German word.</font>

172
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:13,029
<font face="Comic Sans MS">Yes, perhaps, it is
in any case true</font>

173
00:12:13,064 --> 00:12:16,377
<font face="Comic Sans MS">that I suffered from
compulsions as a child.</font>

174
00:12:16,412 --> 00:12:19,656
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I was completely hysterical
about cleaning</font>

175
00:12:19,691 --> 00:12:21,797
<font face="Comic Sans MS">and could never leave
a room that wasn't</font>

176
00:12:21,831 --> 00:12:23,764
<font face="Comic Sans MS">perfectly neat and clean.</font>

177
00:12:23,799 --> 00:12:26,698
<font face="Comic Sans MS">A standard that was
difficult to maintain</font>

178
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:28,873
<font face="Comic Sans MS">in the walk-in freezer.</font>

179
00:12:28,907 --> 00:12:31,358
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The walk-in freezer?</font>

180
00:12:31,392 --> 00:12:34,119
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The walk-in freezer
on Prospect Avenue.</font>

181
00:12:34,154 --> 00:12:37,433
<font face="Comic Sans MS">The sign has been broken
for forever</font>

182
00:12:37,467 --> 00:12:40,263
<font face="Comic Sans MS">so no one really knew what
the name of the street was.</font>

183
00:13:09,361 --> 00:13:11,536
<font face="Comic Sans MS">I bought the pizzas
from the former owner</font>

184
00:13:11,570 --> 00:13:13,745
<font face="Comic Sans MS">of the walk-in freezer.</font>

185
00:13:13,780 --> 00:13:15,989
<font face="Comic Sans MS">He claimed it was a great deal</font>

186
00:13:16,023 --> 00:13:18,439
<font face="Comic Sans MS">but of course I never managed
to sell them</font>

187
00:13:18,474 --> 00:13:21,546
<font face="Comic Sans MS">so it all became
too much for me.</font>

